The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act establishing permanent standard time within the Commonwealth to promote sleep and
health.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 4 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2020 Official Edition, is
2 hereby amended by striking out section 10 and inserting in place thereof the following section: -
3 Section 10. The standard time within the commonwealth shall be permanent standard
4 time and shall be exempt from the advancement of time as provided by the federal Uniform Time
5 Act of 1966, 15 U.S.C. section 260(a). This section shall apply: to all laws, statutes, orders,
6 decrees, rules and regulations relating to the time of performance of any act by any officer or
7 department of the commonwealth, or of any county, city, town or district thereof, or any other
8 political subdivision thereof; to all laws, statutes, orders, decrees, rules and regulations relating
9 to the time in which any rights shall accrue or determine, or within which any act shall or shall
10 not be performed by any person subject to the jurisdiction of the commonwealth; in all the public
11 schools and in all institutions of the commonwealth, or of any county, city, town or district
1 of 2

12 thereof, or any other political subdivision thereof; and in all contracts or choses in action made or
13 to be performed in the commonwealth.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect: (i) upon enactment by law of a permanent year-
15 round “U.S. Eastern Standard Time” in the states of Connecticut, Massachusetts, New
16 Hampshire, Rhode Island and Vermont, in substantially the same form as section 1; and (ii) upon
17 a date agreed upon by all 5 states.
